main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in the sky over Wayzata, Minnesota on June 15, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were observed for approximately 45 minutes.
The objects were described as one large and one oval-shaped, slightly smaller than a car in size.
The objects were directly overhead and showed slight maneuvering movement, but no lights were seen.
The witness was an astronomy student who had previously reported a similar sighting to the Air Force on April 6, 1965.
The weather conditions at the time were clear with scattered clouds.
sighted object: two unidentified objects, one large and one oval-shaped
